    {
      "id": "796a252955a1347a55af61e0b2ede128dc4cbb23",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-25 00:45:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nrecovery-small test 19a, 19b and conf-sanity test 30b failed.\n\nHi Emoly,\n\nCould you please take a look whether I need back-port other patch(es) between the following ones from master to b2_5?\n\n    LU-3386 lproc: fix \"imports\" output format\n    LU-3386 lproc: improve osc/mdc \"imports\" connect data\n\nFor lustre/obdclass/lprocfs_status.c, git log on master showed that:\n\n    LU-3386 lproc: fix \"imports\" output format\n    LU-4367 ptlrpc: add OBD_CONNECT_UNLINK_CLOSE flag\n    LU-4906 llite: read page from LMV/MDC for readdir\n    LU-2675 obd: remove dead code\n    LU-1330 obdclass: splits server-side procfs handling\n    LU-1778 llite: fix inconsistencies of root squash feature\n    LU-3227 tests: fix for acl test\n    LU-4563 Fix unsafe userspace access in many proc files\n    LU-3319 procfs: fix symlink handling\n    LU-3963 Revert bitops changes\n    LU-3963 cleanup: C89 and build cleanups\n    LU-4596 lprocfs: mdt/*/exports/*/uuid is empty after remount\n    LU-2785 osc: remove unused obd methods\n    LU-3319 lprocfs: client side cleanups\n    LU-3529 lod: create striped directory\n    LU-3319 procfs: update shared server side core proc handling to seq_files\n    LU-946 lprocfs: List open files in filesystem\n    LU-3531 llite: move dir cache to MDC layer\n    LU-3963 libcfs: convert obdecho,obdclass code to atomics\n    LU-3386 lproc: improve osc/mdc \"imports\" connect data\n\nSo, there are 18 commits between the two LU-3386 patches. I'm not sure which one(s) need to be back-ported so as to resolve the regression failures in this patch set. Or, maybe we can fix the failures directly on this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
